This spell enables 1 target (+1 / 4 full Ranks) to
travel over ice and/or snow without slipping or sinking in, as
if it were normal earth and/or rock.  For example, this would
enable climbers to climb icy slopes.  Quadrapeds are treated
as two targets for the purposes of this spell.  In addtion, if
the terrain travelled on is flat ice, each target's TMR is
increased by 1 (+1 / 3 full Ranks) while on the ice.  See 7.3,
Travel on Ice, for additional detail.
