17.6, Enchantments etc.); also it has the Range modifiers of a
heavy crossbow. The ice bolt strikes as an A class weapon
doing D + 4 (+1 / Rank) damage which can stun and inflict
specific grievous injuries. Once the spell is cast the target
gets no magic resistance, but the target's defence is
subtracted from the chance to hit. N.B. Since the effect of
the spell is to create a physical bolt. a double or triple
effect cannot affect damage but may add +10\% and +20\% to the
a460 1

a470 1
\emph{Effects:}
d472 7
a478 8
The Adept may conjure 30 cubic feet ice (+30 / Rank)
in up to 1 + Rank shapes of the Adept's choice.  The shapes
always appear entirely within the range of the Adept and may
not appear above or inside (partially or wholly) any entity. 
Each shape must appear on the ground in a stable fashion (not
about to topple over) and must have a minimum thickness of 6
inches in any part.  When the spell duration expires, the ice
disappears (returns to whence it came).
d484 1
a484 1
\emph{Duration:} Concentration / Maximum of 30 minutes +30 / Rank \\
a489 1
\emph{Effects:}
d491 11
a501 12
The Adept creates a polyhedral iceberg of dimensions
10' high, 10' wide and 10' deep (+2 to each dimension / Rank). 
It may only be successfully created in an existing volume of
liquid sufficient to hold it without it touching the bottom.
8/9 of the Iceberg will be submerged. The Iceberg will be flat
topped and may stably support up to 1 hex of entities (+1 /
Rank) (Additional entities will cause it to roll in the
water). While the Adept is in contract with the Iceberg the
Adept may move the Iceberg at a speed of 5 miles per hour (+1
/ Rank). The Iceberg spell also has a calming effect on the
water around it, reducing the size of all waves up to Rank
feet away by Rank feet.
a512 1
\emph{Effects:}
d514 13
a526 14
This spell immediately halts any damage being taken
due to shock or blood loss and the target gains 1 / Rank to
their chance of recovering from stun or unconsciousness (if
applicable). It will restore a (live) character on negative
endurance to zero, although any further damage will start the
process of shock and bleeding as usual. In addition, if the
target is suffering from the adverse effects of a fright roll
or similar emotional effect, they get a second roll (in some
cases a second resistance roll) to recover from ("or snap out
of") it with +1\% / Rank added to their dice roll. The cause of
the fright or shock may have been magical or otherwise. This
spell may be recast on each target as often as desired. This
spell will not work on regenerating entities (including those
under the effects of a trollskin spell).
a537 1
\emph{Effects:}
d539 10
a548 11
Each entity targeted by this spell must resist or
suffer D-4 (+1 / Rank) damage due to being pierced by flying A
class shards of ice (armour does absorb damage but there is no
AG loss).  This damage may stun. If this spell is doubled the
adept may not double damage but may choose to have the ice
projectiles ignore armour instead. If this spell is tripled,
the adept may roll for a possible A class specific grievous
injury for each target that failed to resist, in addition to
ignoring armour as above (and still doing normal fatigue
damage except as part of the grievous result), or reduce the
targets' resistances as usual.
a559 1
\emph{Effects:}
d561 5
a565 5
This spell projects a blast of intense magical cold
at the target. The ray of cold will impact either on the
target or on the first obstruction blocking the path from the
Adept to the target. Anything struck by the ray must either
resist or suffer D+1 (+1 / Rank) damage.
d571 1
a571 1
\emph{Duration:} Concentration / Maximum of 10 seconds + 10 / Rank \\
a576 1
\emph{Effects:}
d578 43
a620 16
This spell causes the ground within 5' of the Adept
to be instantly covered with 5 inches of conjured  snow
(returns to whence it came when the spell duration expires).
Snowballs then form themselves out of the snow and launch
themselves at a target or targets of the Adepts choice. Up to
1 target (+1 / 4 full Ranks) can be pelted with a flurry of
snowballs each pulse. A different set of targets may be chosen
by the Adept each pulse.  Each target must resist or suffer a
reduction of -1\% (-1 / 2 full Ranks) to their Base Chance of
doing anything while being snowballed and in addition must
make a 4 \x WP roll (3 \x WP if Adept is above Rank 10 in this
spell) to perform any action that involves concentrating (e.g.
casting a spell). Each target need only resist this spell
once. If the Adept leaves the 5' diameter circle of snow while
this spell is in effect, the spell is automatically
dissipated.
d622 1
a622 1
\subsubsection{Wall of Ice (S-14)}
a631 1
\emph{Effects:}
d633 9
a641 9
This spell conjures a wall of ice that is 10' high
(+1 / Rank), 20' long (+2 / Rank) and 2' thick (+1 / 2 full
Ranks), or a pillar 15' high (+1 / Rank) with a 3' diameter
(+1 / Rank). Each rank may only increase a single dimension.
The wall may be uniformly curved up to a half circle. The wall
may not be created on top of an entity, and is subject to the
usual restrictions on physical walls.  The wall is translucent
but not transparent.  When the spell duration expires the ice
returns to whence it came.
d643 1
a643 1
\subsubsection{Weapon of Cold (S-15)}
a652 20
\emph{Effects:}
\end{spelldesc}
The weapon over which the spell is cast becomes
infernally cold without harm to either the weapon or the user
of it. The base chance of hitting with the weapon is increased
by 1 (+1 / Rank) and the damage done by the weapon is
increased by 1 (+1 / 3 full Ranks). This amount of damage is
tripled if the object of the attack is a creature of fire.

\subsubsection{Whiteout (S-16)}

\begin{spelldesc}
\emph{Range:} 20 feet + 5 / Rank \\
\emph{Duration:} 10 minutes + 10 / Rank \\
\emph{Experience Multiple:} 150 \\
\emph{Base Chance:} 30\% \\
\emph{Resist:} May be actively \& passively resisted (Entities in Area) \\
\emph{Storage:} Investment, Ward, Magical Trap \\
\emph{Target:} Area \\
\emph{Effects:}
d654 6
a659 17
The Adept colours everything within Range the colour
of pure white snow. All entities get a resistance to be
unaffected and remain their natural colours. An entity which
views entities and objects that are snow white cannot
distinguish them from the background when over 5' away from
them. Infravision also perceives a uniform cool temperature,
although witchsight will work as usual. If there is sharp
shadowing, or the object or entity moves, the observer gets a
3xPerception check to locate the Entity/Object in order to
target them with ranged attacks (which are made at  -20\%) or
magic. Motionless Entities and Objects not in sharp shadowing
are effectively invisible; they may not be targeted, and
attacks against them are made at -50\% even if the attacker
knows the location of the target (e.g. by having observed them
up until they stopped moving).  Under 5' in range any moving
Entity or object can be seen easily and there are no penalties
to combat
a670 1
\emph{Effects:}
d672 5
a676 5
This spell bestows resistance to cold on one plant
(+1 / Rank) or 25 square feet (+25 / Rank) in one patch of the
same species of plant of the Adepts choice. Plants with this
resistance are immune to the Frostbite spell (q.v.) and will
thrive even in permafrost and arctic temperatures.
a686 1
\emph{Effects:}
d688 27
a714 28
The Adept spends an hour forming a human or animal figure, no larger
than 1 hex in size, out of snow, which must be already present. The
animated sculpture will have the same characteristics as the
sculptured entity, except that all characteristics are reduced by
25\%. This will generally cause abilities to be lessened by a like
amount (e.g. Flying speed is reduced by 25\% (if the entity can fly)
due to Agility being reduced; Damage from attacks is reduced by 25\%
due to Strength reduction, Base Chance to hit is reduced because of
M.D.  reduction, etc.).  Magical abilities are not copied in the
copied form, although quasi-magical abilities may be.  The simulacrum
will not bear a close resemblance to any other figure unless the
figure chosen to be duplicated is present during the ritual. In the
latter instance the figure being duplicated may choose to actively
resist the ritual; otherwise the ritual is non-resistible. The
simulacrum has only animal intelligence, and the Adept may give it
simple instructions or actively concentrate to control its movements
(requires the Adept to perform pass actions). The simulacrum will have
vague inclinations relation to its original (borrowed) form, and
although no longer comprised of snow (it takes on a fleshy appearance,
or whatever is appropriate for the original entity) will have an
adverse reaction to the presence of heat and flame and will take an
additional 2 points from heat and flame attacks. The simulacrum
normally resembles a generic example of its borrowed form except that
it has a snowy sheen to it and is cool to the touch. Clothes,
possessions and suchlike are not duplicated by this ritual. When the
Adepts concentration ceases, the simulacrum will collapse into a pile
of ordinary non-magical snow.

